<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-10T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-10T06:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1767</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-10T19:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1917, 7 p.m</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your April 5, 5 p.m. Minister of Finance informs me Japanese inquired of
                            Dr. Koo as to the nature of Abbott’s visit to China. Lie stated that it
                            was for the purpose of information. No other enquiry is known.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>